        </mml:math>
      </disp-formula>
      <p>where <inline-formula><mml:math id="M6"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>δ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo>-</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math></inline-formula> denotes the negative subset containing the false 5mC modification site samples; <inline-formula><mml:math id="M7"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>δ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo>+</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math></inline-formula>, the positive subset containing the true 5mC modification site samples; and symbol ∪ represents union in the set theory.</p>
      <p>Unbalanced data between the true 5mC modification site samples and the false 5mC modification site samples could more objectively reflect the distribution of 5mC modification in promoters. Therefore, the proportion of positive samples and negative samples was set to about 1:11 in this study. In order to reduce the adverse effects of redundancy and homologous bias, sequences with more than 80% sequence similarity were removed using CD-HIT software.</p>
      <p>Finally, we obtained the benchmark dataset <italic>S</italic><sub>δ</sub> composed of 893,326 methylation sample sequences in promoter regions, of which 69,750 sample sequences belong to the positive sample dataset <inline-formula><mml:math id="M8"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>δ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo>+</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math></inline-formula> and 823,576 sample sequences belong to the negative sample dataset <inline-formula><mml:math id="M9"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>δ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo>-</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math></inline-formula>. To investigate the stability and robustness of the prediction model, we randomly selected 80% data in <inline-formula><mml:math id="M10"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>δ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo>+</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math></inline-formula> and <inline-formula><mml:math id="M11"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>δ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo>-</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math></inline-formula>, respectively, as training set S<sub>1</sub> for constructing and training the prediction model, and remained 20% as independent testing dataset S<sub>2</sub> to test the constructed model (<xref rid="T1" ref-type="table">Table 1</xref>). These datasets can be downloaded from the website <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.jci-bioinfo.cn/iPromoter-5mC/download">http://www.jci-bioinfo.cn/iPromoter-5mC/download</ext-link>.</p>
