      <p>According to the intuitive observation in sub-graphs (A), (B), and (D), when δ = 20, the prediction results generated by the three different methods were the best. In order to distinguish the optimal model obtained by using one-hot, DPF and onehot-DPF, we compared the most important metrics Acc and MCC values, and found that the feature method with the best effect was one-hot, as illustrated in sub-graphs (A) and (D). Therefore, the following analysis and calculation were based on δ with 20, indicating the length of the sample sequence formulated by Equation (1) was 41nt.</p>
